---
title: Curried Turkey Tacos with Mango Salsa with Spiced Crema & Cilantro
description: This ready-in-a-flash spin on taco night is all about harmonious flavor pairings: hearty ground turkey spiced with our warming curry blend, tangy-spicy-sweet mango salsa, and smooth, savory, cumin-spiced crema. Bring everything together in warm flour tortillas, and take mealtime to the next level with a fresh, tropical twist!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/65de4f89565f56a1bd2126b9-227672f3.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/65de4f89565f56a1bd2126b9.pdf
time required: 15 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 630 kcal
  fat: 25 g
  saturated fat: 7 g
  carbohydrates: 57 g
  sugar: 17 g
  protein: 34 g
  fiber: 1 g
  sodium: 1060 mg
cuisine: Asian
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/curried-turkey-tacos-with-mango-salsa-65de4f89565f56a1bd2126b9
author: HelloFresh
servings: 2
course: main course
---

Wash and dry produce. Roughly chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over
medium-high heat. Add @ground turkey{10%ounce}, @chicken stock
concentrate{1}, half the @curry powder{1%tablespoon}, 1 TBSP
water, @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces,
until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

> Use all the curry powder and 2 TBSP water for 4 servings.

While turkey cooks, drain @mango{4%ounce} and @pico de gallo{4%ounce}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine mango, pico de gallo, half the cilantro,
a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon}, and a pinch of @chili flakes{1%teaspoon}
(or more if you want an extra kick!). Taste and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

In a separate small bowl, combine @yogurt{4%tablespoon} and
@cumin{1/4%tsp}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> Be sure to measure the cumin; we sent more.

Wrap @flour tortillas{6} in damp #paper towels{} and microwave until
warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Divide tortillas between plates and fill with curried turkey. Top
with mango salsa, spiced crema, and remaining cilantro. Serve.

> Ground Turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.